{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1778701099,"nonce":"I1m2J1nINUNkl8AeWaiVfv4xkjU=","target":"a04711eddc5cf89fc182e50acca8576fa4dbd657e993624cc90ca12eb93670c2","message":"**Decision:** Production point-mass plant uses `damping = 10.0 N·s/m` with `mass = 1.0 kg` (see `scripts/train_minimax.py:294`).\n\n**Rationale:** k=10 sits in the consensus biomechanical range for intrinsic muscle damping at the hand. The same authorship lineage that used k=0.1 in cs2019 (Crevecoeur + Burdet) reverted to consensus the next year (de Brouwer 2020, k=7), confirming that k=0.1 was a methodological simplification for their H∞ saddle-point analysis, not a biomechanical claim.\n\n| Source | k (N·s/m) | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Liu \u0026 Todorov 2007 (J Neurosci) | **10** | \"Intrinsic muscle damping\" |\n| de Brouwer, Jarrassé, Crevecoeur \u0026 Burdet 2020 (eNeuro) | **7** | Same lineage as cs2019 |\n| Burdet/Franklin rule (B ≈ 5% of K ≈ 200 N/m) | **≈ 10** | Empirical heuristic |\n| Tsuji et al. 1995 (Biol Cybern) | **5–30** | Empirical hand impedance, moderate co-contraction |\n| Crevecoeur, Scott \u0026 Cluff 2019 (J Neurosci) | **0.1** | Two orders below consensus; no biomechanical citation |\n| Todorov 2005 (Neural Comput) | **0** | Plant-level; viscosity in 2nd-order muscle filter only |\n\n**Why cs2019 is the outlier:** cs2019's k=0.1 is defensible only as a frictionless-mass + force-filter simplification chosen to make their analytical H∞ saddle-point tractable. The same authors did not carry this choice forward to de Brouwer 2020. Production rlrmp targets biomechanical realism, so consensus k=10 is appropriate.\n\n**Companion decision record:** `tau_rise = 50 ms` force filter — sibling issue `08c49e3`.\n\n**Related work:**\n- `2e5f643` — existing damping-sweep proposal (deferred; would test deviations from this baseline if it runs).\n- `c99ad9d` — training-methods coord (where regime-couples-with-training concerns are tracked).\n- `1d9ae6f` — meta coord (placeholder cross-ref; ideally this would live on a model-structure coord — see `4dabb63`).\n\n**Sources:**\n- Liu \u0026 Todorov 2007: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC6673117/\n- de Brouwer et al. 2020 (eNeuro): https://www.eneuro.org/content/7/2/ENEURO.0514-19.2020\n- Tsuji et al. 1995: https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/BF00199890\n- Crevecoeur, Scott \u0026 Cluff 2019: https://www.jneurosci.org/content/39/41/8135\n- Todorov 2005: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC1550971/\n\nLabel: `feature` (decision record), `deferred` (not actionable work).","files":null}]}